<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-22T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-22T05:00:00-05:00" n="335" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d335">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/12312:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gunther</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-22T12:00:00+02:00">June 22,
                                    1941—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>570. My 569, June 21 [<hi rend="italic">22</hi>], 9 a.m. General
                            Antonescu has proclaimed full mobilization of the Rumanian land, air and
                            marine forces, and has himself taken command of the combined
                            German-Rumanian forces on the Rumanian front.</p>
                        <p>Mihai Antonescu, formerly Minister without Portfolio, and recently
                            Minister of National Propaganda, has been named Vice President of the
                            Council of Ministers, and is charged with the exercise of the functions
                            of the Leader of the State during General Antonescu’s absence.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gunther</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>